# Title: Potentially Suspicious Event Viewer Child Process
# Author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)
# Date: 2017-03-19
# Level: high
# Description: Detects uncommon or suspicious child processes of "eventvwr.exe" which might indicate a UAC bypass attempt
# MITRE Tactic: Privilege Escalation
# Tags: attack.privilege-escalation, attack.t1548.002, car.2019-04-001
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/process_creation/proc_creation_win_eventvwr_susp_child_process.yml

ParentImage="*\\eventvwr.exe" NOT (Image IN ("*:\\Windows\\System32\\mmc.exe", "*:\\Windows\\System32\\WerFault.exe", "*:\\Windows\\SysWOW64\\WerFault.exe"))